sentences: Sophus Andersen (8 December 1859 – 19 September 1923) was a Danish composer and music critic.
He was the son of composer Fritz Andersen (1829–1910).
He studied composition with composer Thorvald Hansen (1847–1915).
In 1890 he graduated and worked for some years as a teacher.
